{
  "texts": [
    "For models to be accurate, their output should adhere to the best available evidence and remain uncontaminated by political or commercial interests.",
    "Currently, however, LLMs often generate incorrect or misleading statements-sometimes called \"hallucinations.\"",
    "These inaccuracies can occur even when a model's training data includes ground truth and other corrective information.",
    "In medicine, the pursuit of accuracy presents particular challenges because the literature often includes contradictory data and because, even if a model is technically accurate, the right decision for a patient may deviate from established guidelines.",
    "In addition, recent research suggests that the reliability of AI models may deteriorate with time."
  ]
}